<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="studied type specimens">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Studied type specimens.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Panama • 1 ♂, holotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microdon hermetia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermetia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Microdon hermetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Curran; Barro Colorado Island, Canal Zone; 23 Dec. 1928; C.H. Curran leg; AMNH. Label 1: &quot;Barro Colo Isld. / Canal Zone / XII-23-1928&quot;; label 2: &quot;Collector / C.H. Curran&quot;; label 3 (red): &quot;Microdon / hermetia / Curran. [male sign] / Holotype&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 16 mm. The constricted abdomen, absence of a triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum, and partly dark wings place this species in a group with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diaphanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. diaphanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by tergite 2 being wider than long, from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. elongatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of yellow in the vena spuria, from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. hermetoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="hermetoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. hermetoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the partly hyaline wing cell bm. The male genitalia are figured in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 256–261" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figures 256 - 261. Male genitalia of Peradon species 256 P. fenestratus French Guyana MNHN 257 P. aureoscutus holotype 258 P. aureus Ecuador CNC 259 P. trilinea holotype 260 P. trivittatus Suriname RMNH 261 P. hermetia holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362314" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261">Fig. 261</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
